      <title>Nivoslider embeded into Ezflow Block</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/nivoslider/forum/general/nivoslider_embeded_into_ezflow_block</link>
      <description>Is it possible to embed nivoslider into block on front page?&#13;
So far I created:&#13;
block.ini.append.php&#13;
&lt;code&gt;&#13;
     [General]&#13;
AllowedTypes[]=NivoSlider&#13;
 &#13;
[NivoSlider]&#13;
Name=NivoSlider&#13;
NumberOfValidItems=9&#13;
NumberOfArchivedItems=5&#13;
ManualAddingOfItems=enabled&#13;
FetchClass=eZFlowMCFetch&#13;
FetchParameters[Source]=NodeID&#13;
FetchParametersSelectionType[Source]=single&#13;
FetchParametersIsRequired[Source]=true&#13;
FetchParameters[Classes]=string&#13;
ViewList[]=nivoslider&#13;
ViewName[nivoslider]=NivoSlider&#13;
 &#13;
&#13;
 &lt;/code&gt;&#13;
&#13;
and added to overide.ini.php&#13;
&#13;
&lt;code&gt;&#13;
   [block_nivoslider]&#13;
Source=block/view/view.tpl&#13;
MatchFile=block/nivoslider.tpl&#13;
Subdir=templates&#13;
Match[type]=NivoSlider&#13;
Match[view]=nivoslider&#13;
 &lt;/code&gt;&#13;
&#13;
so I could have a block which  could be added to frontpage&#13;
Now the first question is do I have to insert NivoSlider object into block or folder containing Nivoslide object?&#13;
And my biggest problem is block/nivoslider.tpl so far I could not make it work.&#13;
I noticed that there is block_item view. What usage is for it?&#13;
&#13;
Nivoslider embeded in XMLblock displaying correctly.&#13;
Best Regards&#13;
Peter&#13;
</description>
