&#13;
about problem &#13;
&#13;
1 - REMOVE THE TEMPLATE OVERRIDE FOR THE FULL VIEW&#13;
i did know about that and i was searching a nice workaraund, but unfortunaly i didnt find that, the only way to solve it is to move the code of full view from the override.ini.append of this extentison to override.ini.append.php  in every siteacces (excluding admin siteacces). &#13;
If someone know how to put an template for a full view in an extension without modify the ini siteacces please let me know, Thanks.&#13;
&#13;
2 - TYPO IN THE EMBED TEMPLATE&#13;
which kind of bug you retrive?&#13;
&#13;
3- TYPO IN THE EMBED TEMPLATE&#13;
i will change this line with the one post ,&#13;
about your problem, can i know if the url of your website is in that form :&#13;
&#13;
www.website.com/&lt;b&gt;INDEX.PHP&lt;/b&gt;/testfolder/..... &#13;
&#13;
or is &#13;
&#13;
www.website.com/testfolder/..... &#13;
&#13;
with out without index.php ? beacuse many people are installing ez without using the correct virtualhost , and so the SiteURL in site.ini is wrong and then the ezurl fuction make some confiuson.&#13;
&#13;
&#13;
thankyou again &#13;
