    <item>
      <title>3 problems solved</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/nivoslider/forum/bugs_and_problems/3_problems_solved</link>
      <description>First of all, thanks for developing this useful extension :-)&#13;
Below a few comments on the issues i found and solved during installation on ez&#13;
&#13;
1 - REMOVE THE TEMPLATE OVERRIDE FOR THE FULL VIEW&#13;
Otherwise you won't see the full view in admin...so you won't be able to manage contents !!!&#13;
&#13;
2 - TYPO IN THE EMBED TEMPLATE part1&#13;
{attribute_view_gui attribute=$object.data_map.effect}  seems to cause a bug&#13;
I personnaly forced one value (slideInLeft) in the template : &#13;
&lt;code&gt;&#13;
&lt;script type="text/javascript"&gt;&#13;
            $(window).load(function() {ldelim}&#13;
                $('#slider').nivoSlider(&#13;
                    {ldelim}&#13;
                    effect : 'slideInLeft',       &#13;
                    slices : {attribute_view_gui attribute=$object.data_map.slices},&#13;
&lt;/code&gt;&#13;
&#13;
3-  TYPO IN THE EMBED TEMPLATE part2&#13;
This path to the image did not work for me :&#13;
&lt;code&gt;&#13;
"{$child.data_map.image.content[nivoslider_block_item].url|ezurl('no','full')}" &#13;
&lt;/code&gt;&#13;
&#13;
I modified it to : &#13;
&lt;code&gt;&#13;
src="{$child.data_map.image.content.nivoslider_embed.full_path}" &#13;
&lt;/code&gt;&#13;
&#13;
&#13;
Appart from those 3 issues, the extension seem to work like a charm.&#13;
I hope this will help further versions/installations :-)&#13;
&#13;
Mickael</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Mickael Robin)</author>
      <guid>http://projects.ez.no/nivoslider/forum/bugs_and_problems/3_problems_solved</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 20 Jan 2012 12:16:17 +0000</pubDate>
    </item>
